<font color="#ff0000">MAN ON P.A.:</font> Attention Heaven Inc...

02:06.835 --> 02:09.235
Morning shift starts now.

02:10.872 --> 02:12.472
More budget cuts.

02:12.508 --> 02:18.345
♪

02:18.380 --> 02:23.850
♪

02:23.886 --> 02:27.120
And in this next constellation,
as you can see,

02:27.155 --> 02:30.690
if you connect all of the dots,
you get...

02:30.726 --> 02:32.079
a bear!

02:32.115 --> 02:33.927
What?

02:33.962 --> 02:36.530
He's the VP's nephew.

02:36.565 --> 02:38.698
Oh.

02:38.734 --> 02:40.534
A really big bear!

02:42.738 --> 02:44.671
<font color="#ffff00">(SIREN WAILS)</font>

02:44.706 --> 02:54.281
♪

02:54.316 --> 02:57.250
<font color="#ff0000">GAIL:</font> <font color="#ffff00">(SIGHS)</font> Okay, Eliza Hunter.

02:57.286 --> 02:59.286
So, you've applied for a transfer.

02:59.321 --> 03:00.987
What is wrong with the...

03:01.023 --> 03:03.323
Department of Dirt?
Oh, nothing.

03:03.358 --> 03:05.759
It has been a really rewarding experience

03:05.794 --> 03:09.329
making millions of tiny
dirt clumps and wetting them,

03:09.364 --> 03:12.532
drying them, watching them blow away,

03:12.568 --> 03:15.001
but I think I might be ready

03:15.037 --> 03:16.336
for a little more responsibility.

03:16.371 --> 03:17.704
Why is that? The Department of Dirt

03:17.739 --> 03:19.606
is one of the most stable jobs
we've got here.

03:19.641 --> 03:22.375
Mark worked in the Department
of Dirt for 80,000 years.

03:22.411 --> 03:26.212
Got his pension, has a
very nice condo, and he's happy.

03:26.248 --> 03:27.781
I know. I'm really happy for Mark.

03:27.816 --> 03:29.449
I just...

03:29.484 --> 03:32.352
I just feel like there's a lot
of big problems down on Earth,

03:32.387 --> 03:34.220
and I want to do more to help.

03:34.256 --> 03:36.089
Eliza, I know you're new here,

03:36.124 --> 03:37.924
but there's something
you've got to understand.

03:37.960 --> 03:39.359
It's way too late to fix Earth.

03:39.394 --> 03:40.961
It's not 30,000 B.C. anymore.

03:40.996 --> 03:43.663
It's not 20 jacked naked people
and a bunch of rockin' dinosaurs

03:43.699 --> 03:45.665
gettin' nasty in
some sick-ass cave somewhere.

03:45.701 --> 03:47.467
I don't... I don't think
that's how that was.

03:47.502 --> 03:49.235
My point is, you can't fix Earth.

03:49.880 --> 03:51.771
Not if you don't give me a shot.

03:51.807 --> 03:55.575
♪

03:55.611 --> 03:57.577
Okay. Fine.

03:57.613 --> 04:01.381
I will transfer you to the
Department of Answered Prayers.

04:01.416 --> 04:03.683
Wait, there's a department
that answers prayers?

04:03.719 --> 04:04.851
Mm-hmm.
Thank you.

04:04.886 --> 04:05.885
<font color="#ffff00">(GASPS)</font>

04:05.921 --> 04:07.520
I can't wait to see it.

04:07.556 --> 04:09.556
<font color="#ffff00">(WATER DRIPPING)</font>

04:11.000 --> 04:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:21.303 --> 04:22.902
<font color="#ffff00">(DOOR CLOSES)</font>
Hello?

04:22.938 --> 04:24.337
<font color="#ffff00">(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

04:24.373 --> 04:26.439
<font color="#ffff00">(KEYBOARD CLACKS, BEEPING)</font>

04:26.475 --> 04:28.375
Hello?

04:28.410 --> 04:29.943
Dividing all that... Hello?

04:29.978 --> 04:31.511
Aah!
Whoa, whoa! Hey, hey!

04:31.546 --> 04:33.046
Hey, it's cool. I'm cool.
Oh.

04:33.081 --> 04:34.848
They just transferred me from Dirt.

04:34.883 --> 04:36.049
I'm Eliza.

04:36.084 --> 04:37.260
Oh.

04:37.919 --> 04:39.285
Oh, wow. Oh, well, welcome!

04:39.321 --> 04:40.954
Sorry. I'm Craig. I'm
so sorry for screaming at you.

04:40.989 --> 04:43.757
I've been alone for years.
And I wasn't expecting anyone.

04:43.792 --> 04:45.025
It's all good.

04:45.060 --> 04:46.993
It is a little dark in here, huh?

04:47.029 --> 04:48.561
I-I-I don't know.

04:48.597 --> 04:50.630
<font color="#ffff00">(BANG)</font>
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> Lights are on.

04:50.666 --> 04:52.632
All right, so, which prayer
do we answer first?

04:52.668 --> 04:54.701
Saving a life, curing a disease...?

04:54.736 --> 04:56.503
You have arrived at a great moment.

04:56.538 --> 04:59.072
This one is set to be a nail-biter.

04:59.107 --> 05:00.473
All right.

05:01.376 --> 05:03.443
Please let me find my car keys.

05:03.478 --> 05:04.978
Keys.

05:05.013 --> 05:06.346
Okay, yeah, guess we gotta get

05:06.381 --> 05:07.480
this little one out of the way.

05:07.516 --> 05:09.182
Let's zap her the keys.
Oh, no.

05:09.217 --> 05:11.351
We can't break the laws of physics.

05:11.386 --> 05:13.053
No zapping. No flying.

05:13.088 --> 05:14.387
Nothing they're gonna notice.

05:14.423 --> 05:16.256
So how do we answer prayers?

05:16.291 --> 05:19.993
Discreet, natural phenomena.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.728
Ha ha ha.

05:21.763 --> 05:23.296
Sneaky, sneaky.

05:23.331 --> 05:26.299
Teasing me from beneath the snow.

05:26.334 --> 05:29.769
Ah, but you can't hide from Papa.

05:29.805 --> 05:32.839
No, Papa sees you.

05:32.874 --> 05:34.607
And Papa is coming for you.

05:34.643 --> 05:36.843
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> One snowflake melted.

05:36.878 --> 05:39.479
<font color="#ffff00">(KEYBOARD CLACKS)</font>
Two snowflakes melted.

05:39.514 --> 05:41.881
I'm sorry. How much longer
is this gonna...

05:41.917 --> 05:45.819
900,317 snowflakes melted.

05:45.854 --> 05:48.488
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN #2:</font> My keys!
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN #1:</font> Prayer complete.

05:48.523 --> 05:51.925
Okay, okay. So, now we move
onto something bigger...?

05:51.960 --> 05:54.294
Well, no, no, no. We're not done yet.

05:54.329 --> 05:56.196
Here's something fun.

05:56.231 --> 05:58.198
And you can put it on the wall.

05:58.233 --> 05:59.899
Uh, let's see. We've got lost keys...

05:59.935 --> 06:01.968
lost keys... lost keys.

06:02.003 --> 06:03.169
A lot of lost keys this month.

06:03.205 --> 06:05.138
Ah! I found a good one.
What?

06:05.173 --> 06:06.306
Let's see.

06:06.341 --> 06:08.374
<font color="#ffff00">(SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN)</font> _

06:08.410 --> 06:09.943
Okay, let's get started. Um...

06:09.978 --> 06:12.312
Oh, uh, I'll handle this.

06:13.014 --> 06:14.047
Wha...
<font color="#ffff00">(SCREAMS)</font>

06:14.082 --> 06:15.215
Whoa! You're just gonna let

06:15.250 --> 06:16.750
those wolves go to town on that guy?

06:16.785 --> 06:18.551
I find it's best
to stick with the small ones.

06:18.587 --> 06:20.854
But don't worry. "Impossibles"
go all the way to the top.

06:20.889 --> 06:23.723
And so, if anyone
can handle them, he can.

06:23.759 --> 06:25.492
Oh, okay.

06:29.364 --> 06:32.298
<font color="#ffff00">(GRUNTS)</font> Ahh! Jordan!

06:33.235 --> 06:34.968
Damn it!

06:35.003 --> 06:36.970
<font color="#ffff00">(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS)</font>

06:37.005 --> 06:40.707
God, I know it's been
a rough few thousand years,

06:40.742 --> 06:42.842
but I think you're being
too hard on yourself.

06:42.878 --> 06:45.445
You know, you've still got
a lot of fans down there.

06:45.480 --> 06:47.280
Not like before.

06:47.315 --> 06:50.183
Do you know how long it's been since
someone sacrificed a ram to me?

06:50.218 --> 06:51.518
I thought that grossed you out.

06:51.553 --> 06:52.752
You know, it did. But at the same time,

06:52.788 --> 06:54.754
there was something nice about it.

06:54.790 --> 06:56.990
I mean, it made me feel like, you know,

06:57.025 --> 06:59.092
hey, I'm doing all right.
Mm.

06:59.127 --> 07:02.996
Now sometimes I just
feel like packing it all in

07:03.031 --> 07:04.697
and moving on to the next thing.
<font color="#ffff00">(BELL TOLLING)</font>

07:04.733 --> 07:06.332
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

07:06.368 --> 07:08.536
Let's, uh... Let's not do
anything drastic, you know?

07:08.572 --> 07:10.036
Let's give it a beat.

07:10.071 --> 07:11.604
Things will improve.

07:11.640 --> 07:12.806
They better.

07:12.841 --> 07:14.812
♪

07:14.847 --> 07:16.609
Impossible.

07:19.113 --> 07:20.513
Impossible.

07:20.782 --> 07:23.716
<font color="#ffff00">(RUMBLING)</font>
Oh! Incoming!

07:23.752 --> 07:24.818
<font color="#ffff00">(BELL RINGS)</font>

07:24.853 --> 07:27.220
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> 2 million prayers received.

07:27.255 --> 07:29.823
This department seems
wildly understaffed!

07:29.858 --> 07:32.725
It was designed to accommodate
a much smaller Earth population.

07:32.761 --> 07:34.828
No one ever imagined the planet
was gonna get this crowded.

07:34.863 --> 07:36.396
There's no way we can answer
all of those.

07:36.431 --> 07:38.698
I generally try and shoot
for three, four a day.

07:38.733 --> 07:40.800
Although, now that
I've got you, a teammate,

07:40.836 --> 07:42.168
there's no telling what we can do.

07:42.204 --> 07:44.270
I'm thinking five... six...

07:44.306 --> 07:46.573
Maybe as many as six!

07:47.909 --> 07:49.576
<font color="#ffff00">(DOOR CLOSES)</font>

07:50.412 --> 07:52.572
<font color="#ff0000">CRAIG:</font> Hyah! Hyah!

07:52.607 --> 07:54.699
Oh! _

07:54.734 --> 07:57.684
♪

07:57.719 --> 07:59.152
Uhh!

07:59.187 --> 08:01.287
Uhh! Uhh!

08:01.323 --> 08:03.022
Uhh! Hyah! Ha!

08:03.058 --> 08:04.257
Oh!

08:04.292 --> 08:08.094
♪

08:08.129 --> 08:09.329
<font color="#ffff00">(BEEP)</font>

08:09.364 --> 08:11.464
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> Rain sequence initiated.

08:11.499 --> 08:12.899
<font color="#ffff00">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

08:14.336 --> 08:17.070
<font color="#ffff00">(LAUGHS)</font>

08:17.105 --> 08:19.539
<font color="#ffff00">(GASPS)</font> Yes!

08:19.574 --> 08:21.140
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> Prayer complete.

08:21.176 --> 08:24.577
<font color="#ffff00">(ALARM BLARING)</font>

08:25.247 --> 08:27.447
No!

08:27.482 --> 08:28.982
What happened? What did you do?

08:29.017 --> 08:30.216
Is that a good alarm?

08:30.252 --> 08:33.119
Wails of grief intermingle with
the shrieking of the death winds

08:33.154 --> 08:36.054
as the typhoon rages on,
taking the lives,

08:36.091 --> 08:37.457
and dignity, of thousands.

08:37.491 --> 08:38.924
There's gotta be something we can do.

08:38.960 --> 08:40.693
I mean, you can press F7.
Does that stop typhoons?

08:40.729 --> 08:42.061
No, it turns the sound off.

08:42.097 --> 08:43.630
...this is horrible...
<font color="#ff0000">WOMAN:</font> Mute.

08:43.664 --> 08:45.999
Oh.
Overflow. Overflow.

08:46.034 --> 08:48.134
Don't beat yourself up.
Hey, it's your first day.

08:48.169 --> 08:50.603
We all make mistakes.
Oh, here's something fun...

08:50.639 --> 08:52.372
Related prayers
all come out together bundled.

08:52.407 --> 08:53.506
It's a way to speed... What do they say?!

08:53.541 --> 08:54.774
Oh, well, yeah, you know...

08:54.809 --> 08:55.909
"Please save me," "Please save me,"

08:55.944 --> 08:57.143
"Save me," "Please save me."

08:57.178 --> 08:59.112
"Please kill me."

08:59.147 --> 09:00.914
That's pretty chilling.

09:00.949 --> 09:03.283
Come on, we gotta get these up there!

09:03.318 --> 09:05.585
Oh, n... Don't. Okay.
Prayer jam.

09:05.620 --> 09:07.320
Maybe if I can unclog the tube...

09:07.355 --> 09:09.055
Ooh. Missing glove!

09:09.090 --> 09:10.356
<font color="#ffff00">(KEYBOARD CLACKS, BEEPS)</font>

09:10.392 --> 09:13.259
<font color="#ffff00">(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS)</font>

09:13.295 --> 09:17.297
♪

09:17.332 --> 09:19.232
Uh, where are you going?

09:19.267 --> 09:20.500
To fix this.

09:20.535 --> 09:23.503
<font color="#ffff00">(ALARM BLARING)</font>
Tragedy. Tragedy.

09:23.538 --> 09:25.939
Tragedy. Tragedy.

09:25.974 --> 09:28.608
Tragedy. Tragedy.

09:28.643 --> 09:32.745
Oh, Lazy Susan, love of my life.

09:32.781 --> 09:34.948
If only everything worked as good as you.

09:34.983 --> 09:36.616
<font color="#ffff00">(DOOR SLAMS OPENS)</font>

09:36.651 --> 09:39.118
I'm sorry, sir. I told her you were busy.

09:39.688 --> 09:41.020
It's all good.

09:43.625 --> 09:45.066
Hey.

09:45.101 --> 09:46.194
God.

09:47.716 --> 09:49.382
Hi. Hi.

09:49.490 --> 09:51.624
Eliza. What's up?

09:51.779 --> 09:54.914
Okay, there is a crazy typhoon happening,

09:54.939 --> 09:56.739
and it's killing lots of people.

09:56.838 --> 09:58.004
Can you help?

09:58.039 --> 10:01.084
I don't want to sound cynical,
but what's the point?

10:01.676 --> 10:04.911
Uh, the point is, you're God.

10:05.338 --> 10:08.381
You made Earth, okay? It is yours.

10:08.416 --> 10:11.046
And right now, it is in big, big trouble.

10:11.082 --> 10:13.086
It is a mess! People are dying!

10:13.121 --> 10:15.722
And you... you are
the only one that can fix it.

10:15.757 --> 10:18.124
Please, you have got to do something.

10:20.979 --> 10:22.522
You know what?

10:23.565 --> 10:25.264
You're right.

10:25.300 --> 10:27.834
♪

10:27.869 --> 10:30.803
<font color="#ffff00">(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)</font>

10:30.839 --> 10:32.805
I've been here 10,000 years.

10:32.841 --> 10:35.008
He's never addressed
the whole company before.

10:35.043 --> 10:36.009
<font color="#ffff00">(FEEDBACK)</font>

10:36.044 --> 10:38.411
Hi.
<font color="#ffff00">(FEEDBACK, CROWD GROANING)</font>

10:38.446 --> 10:40.546
Sorry, guys. Sorry.

10:40.582 --> 10:42.142
Is that God?

10:42.177 --> 10:43.816
Um...

10:43.852 --> 10:45.774
Can they hear me?
Yeah. Just lean in.

10:45.810 --> 10:47.787
Yeah. Um...

10:47.822 --> 10:52.025
so, I've decided to blow up Earth.

10:52.060 --> 10:53.226
<font color="#ffff00">(CROWD GASPS)</font>

10:55.002 --> 10:56.969
And, uh...

10:56.994 --> 10:58.194
I guess that's it.

10:58.219 --> 10:59.225
All right.

11:01.202 --> 11:02.835
<font color="#ffff00">(WHISTLE BLOWS)</font>

11:04.605 --> 11:07.932
So, uh, just to be totally clear...

11:07.968 --> 11:12.136
you want to destroy the entire
world and kill everyone?

11:12.171 --> 11:14.069
Yeah. But that's not why
I brought you in here.

11:14.104 --> 11:16.054
We have something bigger to discuss...

11:16.092 --> 11:17.619
my next thing.

11:18.027 --> 11:21.062
I bet you a hundo
you can't guess what it is.

11:22.198 --> 11:25.266
♪

11:25.301 --> 11:26.667
Is it a new planet?

11:26.703 --> 11:27.802
You owe me a hundo!

11:27.837 --> 11:29.937
This here is a restaurant.

11:29.973 --> 11:33.174
What?
I call it... Lazy Susan's.

11:33.209 --> 11:36.511
Okay, what two things
do people love the most?

11:36.546 --> 11:38.412
Uh...
Great food.

11:38.448 --> 11:40.481
And lazy rivers. Right?

11:40.517 --> 11:41.849
Here's how it works.

11:41.885 --> 11:45.219
The outside is a lazy river.

11:45.255 --> 11:47.789
And the middle part here
is an island that has, you know,

11:47.824 --> 11:51.092
like, all these great chefs
making all kinds of food.

11:51.127 --> 11:53.961
Now, you, you're
floating around with, uh,

11:53.997 --> 11:57.031
some sort of a claw-type device, right?

11:57.066 --> 11:58.666
And when you see a food you like,

11:58.701 --> 12:00.768
you just reach out with your claw,

12:00.804 --> 12:03.271
and you grab it with your claw.

12:03.306 --> 12:05.139
Couple of questions. Shoot.

12:05.175 --> 12:09.443
If you're blowing up the Earth,
where will the restaurant be?

12:09.479 --> 12:12.079
Space? Somewhere in space?

12:12.115 --> 12:13.714
I don't know. That's your department.

12:13.750 --> 12:15.516
Oh. I'm involved.

12:15.552 --> 12:18.252
We are really doing something.

12:18.288 --> 12:19.722
Something amazing.

12:21.191 --> 12:22.475
I love you, buddy.

12:23.426 --> 12:24.894
I love you.

12:25.829 --> 12:28.629
<font color="#ff0000">MAN ON P.A.:</font> Reminder...
All departments are responsible

